The paper presents a new algorithm for distance oracle for road networks, which involves graph theory, optimization, and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it deals with the design and analysis of efficient algorithms and data structures. The paper also involves optimization techniques, which makes cs.RO (Robotics and Control) a likely category. The use of machine learning techniques for locality filtering makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques for locality filtering, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves the use of specialized algorithms for online many-to-one (or one-to-many) shortest path, which makes cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible category.
